				\begin{document}$$\varDelta {E}_{{\rm{enhancement}}}=\frac{\varDelta {h}_{{\rm{MOHCs}}}-\varDelta {h}_{{\rm{MOHCs}},x=0,{\rm{293K}}}}{\varDelta {h}_{{\rm{MOHCs}},x=0,{\rm{293K}}}}$$\end{document}where ∆Eenhancement represents the increase in energy storage. ∆hMOHCs,x=0,293K is the energy difference (∆hMOHCs) of the discussed refrigerant with the mass fraction of MOHCs x = 0 at 293 K.

Then the adsorption selectivity was calculated to assess the adsorption capacity of a sorbent in mixture competitive adsorption simulations. The adsorption selectivity of sorbent A over sorbent B in M-MOF-74 was defined as,4SA=xA/yAxB/yB\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
